    "HARSHLY": "In a harsh manner; gratingly; roughly; rudely.'T will sound harshly in her ears. Shak.",
    "HARSHNESS": "The quality or state of being harsh.O, she is Ten times more gentle than her father 's crabbed, And he'scomposed of harshness. Shak.'Tis not enough no harshness gives offense, The sound must seem anecho to the sense. Pope.",
    "HARSLET": "See Haslet.",
    "HART": "A stag; the male of the red deer. See the Note under Buck.Goodliest of all the forest, hart and hind. Milton.",
