    "HATTER": "To tire or worry; -- out. [Obs.] Dryden.",
    "HATTERIA": "A New Zealand lizard, which, in anatomical character, differswidely from all other existing lizards. It is the only livingrepresentative of the order Rhynchocephala, of which many Mesozoicfossil species are known; -- called also Sphenodon, and Tuatera.",
