    "HAUNCHED": "Having haunches.",
    "HAUNT": "To persist in staying or visiting.I've charged thee not to haunt about my doors. Shak.",
    "HAUNTED": "Inhabited by, or subject to the visits of, apparitions;frequented by a ghost.All houses wherein men have lived and died Are haunted houses.Longfellow.",
    "HAUNTER": "One who, or that which, haunts.",
    "HAURIENT": "In pale, with the head in chief; -- said of the figure of afish, as if rising for air.",
    "HAUSEN": "A large sturgeon (Acipenser huso) from the region of the BlackSea. It is sometimes twelve feet long.",
