    "HAUSTORIUM": "One of the suckerlike rootlets of such plants as the dodder andivy. R. Brown.",
    "HAUT": "Haughty. [Obs.] \"Nations proud and haut.\" Milton.",
    "HAUTBOY": "A wind instrument, sounded through a reed, and similar in shapeto the clarinet, but with a thinner tone. Now more commonly calledoboe. See Illust. of Oboe.",
