    "HERMAPHRODEITY": "Hermaphrodism. B. Jonson.",
    "HERMAPHRODISM": "See Hermaphroditism.",
    "HERMAPHRODITE": "An individual which has the attributes of both male and female,or which unites in itself the two sexes; an animal or plant havingthe parts of generation of both sexes, as when a flower contains boththe stamens and pistil within the same calyx, or on the samereceptacle. In some cases reproduction may take place without theunion of the distinct individuals. In the animal kingdom truehermaphrodites are found only among the invertebrates. See Illust. inAppendix, under Helminths.",
    "HERMAPHRODITISM": "The union of the two sexes in the same individual, or thecombination of some of their characteristics or organs in oneindividual.",
    "HERMENEUTICALLY": "According to the principles of interpretation; as, a verse ofScripture was examined hermeneutically.",
    "HERMENEUTICS": "The science of interpretation and explanation; exegesis; esp.,that branch of theology which defines the laws whereby the meaning ofthe Scriptures is to be ascertained. Schaff-Herzog Encyc.",
