    "HYDROSULPHURET": "A hydrosulphide. [Archaic]",
    "HYDROSULPHURETED": "Combined with hydrogen sulphide.",
    "HYDROSULPHURIC": "Pertaining to, or derived from, hydrogen and sulphur; as,hydrosulphuricacid, a designation applied to the solution of hydrogensulphide in water.",
    "HYDROSULPHUROUS": "Pertaining to, or designating, an acid obtained by thereduction of sulphurous acid. See Hyposulphurous acid, underHyposulphurous.",
    "HYDROTELLURATE": "A salt formed by the union of hydrotelluric acid and the base.",
